-- Alfa Bank’s Ukrainian Unit Repays $115.3 Million on Eurobonds
-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 2012-01-27T10:02:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/alfa-bank-s-ukrainian-unit-repays-115-3-million-on-eurobonds.html
Alfa Bank’s Ukrainian unit repaid
$115.3 million as the sixth tranche on its Eurobonds due in
2012.  The Kiev-based PAO Alfa Bank Ukraine paid a coupon of $10.2
million and principal of $105.1 million yesterday, the lender
said in an e-mailed statement today.  Investors agreed to change Alfa Bank’s Eurobonds maturing
in 2009, 2010 and 2011 into new securities due this year in
August 2009. The bank has repaid 75 percent of the total volume
of new $840.63 million Eurobonds so far, according to the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
